cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a novel attention gate model for medical imaging, which is a combination of computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the integration of the attention gate model into standard CNN architectures, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for automatically learning to focus on target structures, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed architecture is evaluated on two large CT abdominal datasets, which involves medical image analysis and could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
